quran[96]{c,v,t}:
  56,1,When the inevitable event comes to pass
  56,2,Then will no soul entertain falsehood concerning its coming
  56,3,"Many will it bring low, many will it exalt"
  56,4,When the earth will be shaken to its depths
  56,5,And the mountains will be crumbled to atoms
  56,6,Becoming dust scattered abroad
  56,7,And you will be sorted out into three classes
  56,8,"The companions of the right, what are the companions of the right"
  56,9,"And the companions of the left, what are the companions of the left"
  56,10,"And those foremost, will be foremost"
  56,11,These will be those nearest to God
  56,12,In gardens of bliss
  56,13,A number of people from those of the past
  56,14,And a few from those of later times
  56,15,On thrones encrusted
  56,16,"Reclining on them, facing each other"
  56,17,Around them will be youth of perpetual innocence
  56,18,"With goblets, bowls, and cups filled from clear-flowing fountains"
  56,19,"No after-ache will they receive from it, nor will they suffer intoxication"
  56,20,"And fruits, any they may select"
  56,21,"And the meat of fowl, any that they may desire"
  56,22,And companions with beautiful eyes
  56,23,Like pearls well guarded
  56,24,A reward for the deeds of their past
  56,25,"Neither frivolousness will they hear therein, nor any taint of harm"
  56,26,"Only the saying, “Peace, peace.”"
  56,27,"The companions of the right hand, what are the companions of the right hand"
  56,28,They will be among lotus trees without thorns
  56,29,Among Talh trees with flowers piled one above another
  56,30,In shade long extended
  56,31,By water flowing constantly
  56,32,And fruit in abundance
  56,33,"Whose season is not limited, nor prevented"
  56,34,"And on thrones, raised high"
  56,35,We have created their companions of a special creation
  56,36,And made them virgin - pure
  56,37,"Beloved, equal in age"
  56,38,For the companions of the right hand
  56,39,A number from those in the past
  56,40,And a number from those of later times
  56,41,"The companions of the left hand, who will be the companions of the left hand"
  56,42,They will be in the middle of a fierce blast of fire and in boiling water
  56,43,And in the shades of black smoke
  56,44,"Nothing to refresh, or to please them"
  56,45,"Because they were accustomed to indulging, before that, with their wealth"
  56,46,And insisted on great harm
  56,47,"And they used to say, “What, when we die and become dust and bones, will we then indeed be raised up again"
  56,48,“And our ancestors?”
  56,49,"Say, “Yes, those in the past and those of later times"
  56,50,"“All will certainly be gathered together, for the meeting appointed for a day well-known"
  56,51,"“Then will you truly, O you who go wrong by treating truth as falsehood"
  56,52,“You will surely taste of the Tree of Zaqqum
  56,53,“Then and there you will fill your insides
  56,54,“And drink boiling water on top of it
  56,55,“Indeed you will drink like thirsty camels.”
  56,56,Such will be their entertainment on the Day of Punishment
  56,57,It is We Who have created you. Why will you not witness the truth
  56,58,Do you then see that which you throw out
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or are We the Creators"
  56,60,"We have decreed death for you, and We are not to be stopped–"
  56,61,"From changing your forms, and creating you in forms that you know not"
  56,62,And you certainly already know the first form of creation. Why then do you not praise Him
  56,63,Do you see the seed that you sow in the ground
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it to grow, or are We the cause"
  56,65,"Were it Our will, We could crumble it to dry powder, and you would be left in wonderment–"
  56,66,"Saying, “We are indeed left with debts"
  56,67,“Indeed we are shut out.”
  56,68,Do you see the water which you drink
  56,69,Do you bring it down from the cloud or do We
  56,70,"If it were Our will, We could make it salty. So why do you not give thanks"
  56,71,Do you see the fire which you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who causes the tree to grow which feeds the fire, or do We cause it to grow"
  56,73,"We have made it a memorial, an article of comfort, and convenience for the denizens of deserts"
  56,74,"Then glorify with praises the name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  56,75,"Furthermore, I call to witness the setting of the stars"
  56,76,And that is indeed a mighty adjuration if you only knew
  56,77,That this is indeed a Quran most honorable
  56,78,In a book well guarded
  56,79,Which none will touch but those who are clean
  56,80,A revelation from the Guardian Evolver of all the systems of knowledge
  56,81,Is it such a message that you would hold in light esteem
  56,82,And have you made it your life to declare it false
  56,83,Then why do you not intervene when the soul reaches the throat
  56,84,But you just stand there looking on
  56,85,"But We are nearer to him than you, but you see not"
  56,86,"Then why do you not, if you are exempt from account"
  56,87,"Call back the soul, if you are truthful"
  56,88,Then if he is of those nearest to God
  56,89,"There is for him rest and satisfaction, and a garden of pleasure"
  56,90,And if he is of the companions of the right hand
  56,91,"Then for him is the salutation, “Peace be unto you,” from the companions of the right hand"
  56,92,"And if he is of those who treat truth as false, and who go wrong"
  56,93,For him is entertainment with boiling water
  56,94,And burning in hellfire
  56,95,"Indeed, this is the truth with certainty"
  56,96,"So glorify with praises the name of your Lord, the Supreme"